              *********Order By Statement**********


***Order By statement is used for ordering data in Ascending or Descending order***


***Query: Select * From dbo.EmployeeDemographics Order by Age;


*** Conditional Statement***


***Query: Select Gender, Count (Gender) as CountGender From dbo.EmployeeDemographics Where Age >31 Group by Gender Order by Gender


*** Ascending Order**


***Query: Select * from dbo.EmployeeDemographics Order by age asc;


***Dscending Order***


***Query: Select * from dbo.EmployeeDemographics Order by age desc;


*** Both Ascending and Dscending command*** 


***Query: Select * from dbo.EmployeeDemographics Order by age asc, Gender desc;


******We can use column number instead of name in group by statement :


***Query: Select * from dbo.EmployeeDemographics Order by 4 desc, 5 desc;








